        "review earnings update against institutional standards",
        "verify earnings report quality" .

oc:kn_10bd1165 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When adding any data point, figure, or table to the report" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Every figure/table must cite a specific source with document name, date, and page/slide number. Consensus estimates must include 'as of' date (pre-earnings close). Management quotes must cite speaker name and source document." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Source traceability is fundamental to institutional research integrity and enables verification by clients and compliance." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_210027e3 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PreFlightCheck ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Immediately before delivering the earnings update to the user" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Before delivery, verify: (1) all reported numbers match company press release exactly, (2) 3-4 spot-checked citations have sources with clickable hyperlinks, (3) old vs new estimates shown with explanations, (4) all 8-12 charts embedded/numbered/captioned, (5) length is 8-12 pages, (6) data is from the LATEST quarter via active search (not knowledge cutoff)." ;
    oc:hasRationale "A single numerical error or broken hyperlink can destroy analyst credibility; the 5-minute final review catches the most common delivery failures." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_39e8c63a a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When adding any citation, source, or reference URL" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never include plain text URLs — all URLs must be formatted as clickable hyperlinks with meaningful display text, blue underlined styling, and tested functionality." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Plain text URLs are unprofessional and unusable in institutional research documents; clickable hyperlinks are a non-negotiable standard." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_40ae2051 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When updating estimates and price targets post-earnings" ;
    oc:directiveContent "If estimates change >5%, update the price target. If company provides guidance, analyze it thoroughly. If no guidance, explicitly state that. Compare results to peers who have already reported." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Material estimate changes without PT updates signal incomplete analysis; unacknowledged absent guidance creates ambiguity." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_6b955d7b a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When drafting earnings update content" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never write initiation-length reports for quarterly earnings, use vague language like 'strong performance' without quantification, rehash company basics for 3 pages, or publish 5+ days after earnings." ;
    oc:hasRationale "These mistakes waste reader time, reduce report impact, and undermine institutional credibility." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_98e57857 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When formatting the final earnings update report" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Report must be 8-12 pages with 8-12 embedded charts, 1-3 summary tables, Page 1 earnings summary format, and 'EARNINGS UPDATE' in title (not 'Initiating Coverage')." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Consistent format ensures institutional clients can quickly locate key information across multiple analyst reports." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_c57a51b8 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing any earnings update report" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Lead with the beat/miss verdict and quantify everything — e.g., '$150M beat on $1.2B revenue' instead of 'strong results'. Publish within 24-48 hours post-earnings for relevance." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Institutional clients need immediate, quantified takeaways; vague language and delayed publication destroy analyst credibility." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_ee1dd39f a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:KnownIssue ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When gathering data for the earnings update" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Do NOT rely on knowledge cutoff data — actively search for the latest quarter's earnings to ensure all data is current. Verify the earnings release date is within the last 1-3 months." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Using stale data from knowledge cutoff produces irrelevant or incorrect analysis that misleads the reader." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

_:ref_001310484be28374 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Update price target if material**: If estimates change >5%, usually PT changes too" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_6" ;
    oc:stepOrder 6 .

_:ref_1618c99b9054138f a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Acknowledge the call**: Reference management commentary, don't just analyze the press release" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_7" ;
    oc:stepOrder 7 .

_:ref_1b2c5c3e3f158a91 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Quantify everything**: \"Strong\" means nothing, \"$150M beat on $1.2B revenue\" is clear" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_3" ;
    oc:stepOrder 3 .

_:ref_2209c69bda1bcd57 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Compare to peers**: If similar companies reported, note relative performance" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_8" ;
    oc:stepOrder 8 .

_:ref_2d64a0dd7efbf7b0 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Estimates**: Old vs. new clearly shown? Changes explained?" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_4" ;
    oc:stepOrder 4 .

_:ref_3023b821714938d8 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Hyperlinks**: Test 3-4 hyperlinks - do they work with Ctrl+Click?" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_7" ;
    oc:stepOrder 7 .

_:ref_37c6211b74ed6b0b a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Show the work**: Old estimates → New estimates with reasons" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_5" ;
    oc:stepOrder 5 .

_:ref_44ce11df320cc8b1 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Chart the trends**: Quarterly progression charts are most valuable" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_10" ;
    oc:stepOrder 10 .

_:ref_4f5e7e1407b01fb8 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Lead with conclusion**: Beat or miss? Up or down estimates?" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_2" ;
    oc:stepOrder 2 .

_:ref_53bfe377a6662cf0 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Page 1**: Rating clear? Price target updated? Key takeaways compelling?" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_1" ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

_:ref_85e3397ad49d241b a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Be concise**: This is NOT a comprehensive report, stay focused on quarterly results" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_9" ;
    oc:stepOrder 9 .

_:ref_8f18dd22ecc072b4 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Charts**: All 8-12 embedded? All numbered and captioned?" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_5" ;
    oc:stepOrder 5 .

_:ref_aaae66fce8e02c9a a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Citations**: Spot check 3-4 figures/tables - all have sources with clickable hyperlinks?" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_3" ;
    oc:stepOrder 3 .

_:ref_b4bf3881efb99d51 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Focus on drivers**: Don't just say \"revenue beat\", explain WHY" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_4" ;
    oc:stepOrder 4 .

_:ref_c7d69172d7ab1676 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Length**: Is it 8-12 pages (not 6, not 15)?" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_6" ;
    oc:stepOrder 6 .

_:ref_eb45f515e146e40f a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Speed matters**: Published 24-48hrs post-earnings, not days later" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_1" ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

_:ref_f03ae41cadd23d9b a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Numbers**: Do reported results match company's press release exactly?" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_2" ;
    oc:stepOrder 2 .

_:ref_f07f7509b984af84 a oc:WorkflowStep ;
    dcterms:description "**Timeliness**: Is this being published within 48 hours of earnings?" ;
    oc:blockType "workflow_step" ;
    oc:stepId "step_8" ;
    oc:stepOrder 8 .

